<% provide(:title, "How To") %>
<div class="how-to-page">
  <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid bg-dark text-light text-center howto_intro_div">
    <div class="container">
      <%= image_tag("howto.png", alt: "Hodr Logo", height: "300px", width: "100%") %>
      <h1 class="howto_h1">How To Use Hodr</h1>
      <p class="lead howto_p">
        Discover how quickly &amp; easily you can create a new account, log into your account, edit your account details and much more!
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="how-to-page howto_secondary">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">

        <!-- Create an Account -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Creating an Account</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To create an account on Hodr, follow these simple steps:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Hodr website.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Sign Up" button.</li>
          <li>Fill out the registration form with your information.</li>
          <li>Click "Submit" to create your account.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Log Into Account -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Logging Into Your Account</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To log into your Hodr account:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Hodr website.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Log In" button.</li>
          <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
          <li>Click "Login" to access your account.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Edit Your Account -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Editing Your Account</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To Edit Your Profile:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Hodr website.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Log In" button.</li>
          <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
          <li>Click "Login" to access your account.</li>
          <li>Click on "Account".</li>
          <li>Click on "Settings".</li>
          <li>Fill out information accordingly.</li>
          <i>certain fields are not editable for security &amp; account reasons.</i>
        </ol>

        <!-- Follow Users -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Following Users</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To follow your friends:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Hodr website.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Log In" button.</li>
          <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
          <li>Click "Login" to access your account.</li>
          <li>Click on "Users".</li>
          <li>Scroll through the list and find your friend.</li>
          <li>Click on their username to be taken to their profile.</li>
          <li>Click on "Follow" button on left side under their stats to follow them.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Unfollow Users -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">UnFollowing Users</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To unfollow your friends:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Hodr website.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Log In" button.</li>
          <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
          <li>Click "Login" to access your account.</li>
          <li>Click on "Users".</li>
          <li>Scroll through the list and find your friend.</li>
          <li>Click on their username to be taken to their profile.</li>
          <li>Click on "Unfollow" button on left side under their stats to unfollow them.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Understanding The Profile View Page -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">How Your Page Works</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">Understanding How Your Page Works:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li><strong>Top Section (Banner &amp; Avatar):</strong></li>
          <i>These images are defaulted to the developers choice. If you update your avatar &amp; banner, your
            new images will appear there. These are set so you can have a bit of customization to your profile!</i>
          <li><strong>Profile Navigation (Feed | About | Activities | Career):</strong></li>
          <i>These buttons hide or show each other. For example, if you are seeing your feed section, the other sections
            are hidden. But if you click on About, you will see the about section and not the feed section.</i>
          <li><strong>Feed Section:</strong></li>
          <i>This section is where you can see the posts you had created, as well as the posts from your followers.
            You will not see posts from other users that you do not follow. Also, if you are viewing another persons profile,
            this feed section will only show posts that user has created.</i>
          <li><strong>About Section:</strong></li>
          <i>This section displays your information about you. Including Biography, first, last, middle name, and other
            important information. You choose what you want to share. If you are viewing another persons profile, this tab
            will show their information. But only what they choose to put on the site.</i>
          <li><strong>Activities Section:</strong></li>
          <i>This section covers your favorite activities and hobbies. From the books you read, to the movies and songs you
            enjoy. These are text-based and does not "tag" or "use" your information in here to perform any marketing techniques.</i>
          <li><strong>Career Section:</strong></li>
          <i>This section allows you to showcase the employment of what you are currently doing, as well as your highest level
            of education you have completed.</i>
          <li><strong>The only thing that other users can see about you, and what you see about other people, is what they, or you,
            had put inside of your settings. You are not required to fill everything out. It is at your own choice to fill it out
            or not.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Account Deletion -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Account Deletion</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">If you would like to Delete your Account:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li><strong>Contact an Admin:</strong></li>
          <i>If you want your account to be deleted, please send us an email from the email
            associated with your account. This will help with verification.<br/>
          Admin Email: <%= link_to "Hodr Admin", 'mailto:help.hodr@gmail.com', target: '_blank' %></i>
          <li><strong>Explain the Reason:</strong></li>
          <i>While you can use something short like "I no longer use this site", a more detailed
            explaination would be helpful for our user interactions. This is also to help aid in
            verification of the account deletion.</i>
          <li><strong>Wait for Deletion/Approval:</strong></li>
          <i>While we are investigating the deletion of your account, we will also search through
            your profile. If we notice something that goes against our policies &amp; rules, we
            will take the correct actions. Which can include locking you out of the account and
            reporting your profile to the proper authorities.</i>
        </ol>

        <!-- Using Boards -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Using Boards</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">Learn how to interact with boards on Hodr, create new boards, find and join existing ones, and understand the guidelines for communication.</p>

        <!-- Creating a New Board -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Creating a New Board</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To start your own discussion board:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Log into your Hodr account and navigate to the Boards section.</li>
          <li>Click on the "Create Board" button.</li>
          <li>Fill in the details for your board, including a name, description, and choose a category that best fits the board’s theme.</li>
          <li>Click "Create" to establish your new board. You’re now ready to post messages and invite others to join the discussion!</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Finding and Joining Boards -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Finding and Joining Boards</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To explore and join existing boards:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Visit the Boards section after logging in.</li>
          <li>Use the search function to find boards by name or browse through categories.</li>
          <li>Click on a board name to view its posts. You can join the conversation by clicking "Join Board" if it's public or request an invitation for private boards.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Sending Messages on Boards -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Sending Messages</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">To contribute to a board by sending messages:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li>Open the board you wish to participate in.</li>
          <li>Type your message in the message box and use the formatting tools if needed.</li>
          <li>Click "Send" to post your message. It will now be visible to all board members.</li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Board Etiquette -->
        <h2 class="howto_sec_h2">Board Etiquette and Guidelines</h2>
        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">While interacting on boards, remember to follow Hodr’s community guidelines:</p>
        <ol class="howto_list">
          <li><strong>Be Respectful:</strong> Treat all members with respect. Avoid insults, harassment, or any form of bullying.</li>
          <li><strong>Stay On Topic:</strong> Keep your posts relevant to the board’s theme or ongoing discussions.</li>
          <li><strong>No Profanity or Vulgarity:</strong> Refrain from using offensive language, including profanity, vulgarity, or sexual content. Discussions should comply with the site’s <a href="https://hodr.me/eula" target="_blank">EULA agreement</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Report Issues:</strong> If you encounter any posts or behavior that violates our guidelines, please report them to the moderators or via the "Report" button.</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="text-muted howto_sec_p">
          Boards are a space for meaningful discussions, sharing knowledge, and connecting with others who share your interests. By following these guidelines, you help create a welcoming and positive environment for all members.
        </p>
        
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
